            { id: "ns_m1", q: "What is the general term of a binomial expansion?", a: ["T_r", "T_{r+1}", "T_{n}", "T_{r-1}"], c: 1, e: "The general term in the binomial expansion of (a + x)^n is denoted as T_{r+1} = ⁿC_r · a^{n-r} · x^r." },
            { id: "ns_m2", q: "If A is a symmetric matrix, then A^T is equal to:", a: ["-A", "A", "I", "0"], c: 1, e: "By definition, a square matrix A is symmetric if it is equal to its own transpose, meaning A^T = A." },
            { id: "ns_m3", q: "The multiplicative inverse of the complex number (a, b) is:", a: ["(a/(a²+b²), -b/(a²+b²))", "(-a/(a²+b²), b/(a²+b²))", "(a, -b)", "(-a, -b)"], c: 0, e: "The multiplicative inverse of z = a + ib is 1/z = z̄ / |z|², which simplifies to the coordinate form (a/(a²+b²), -b/(a²+b²))." },
            { id: "ns_m4", q: "If a matrix A has order 3x4, then the order of A^T is:", a: ["3x4", "4x3", "3x3", "4x4"], c: 1, e: "Taking the transpose of a matrix swaps its rows and columns. Thus, a 3x4 matrix becomes a 4x3 matrix." },
            { id: "ns_m5", q: "The determinant of a singular matrix is always:", a: ["1", "-1", "0", "Any real number"], c: 2, e: "A matrix is defined as singular if and only if its determinant is exactly equal to 0, meaning it lacks a multiplicative inverse." },
            { id: "ns_m6", q: "The number of terms in the expansion of (x + y)^n is:", a: ["n", "n-1", "n+1", "2n"], c: 2, e: "In a standard binomial expansion of index 'n', the number of terms is always n + 1 because the power ranges from 0 to n." },
            { id: "ns_m7", q: "If sin(x) = 1/2, then the principal value of x is:", a: ["π/3", "π/6", "π/4", "π/2"], c: 1, e: "The principal domain for sin⁻¹(x) is [-π/2, π/2]. Within this interval, sin(π/6) = 1/2, which corresponds to 30°." },
            { id: "ns_m8", q: "The period of the trigonometric function tan(x) is:", a: ["π", "2π", "π/2", "3π"], c: 0, e: "Unlike sine and cosine functions which have a period of 2π, the fundamental period of tangent and cotangent functions is π." },
            { id: "ns_m9", q: "The sum of the infinite geometric series 1 + 1/2 + 1/4 + 1/8 + ... is:", a: ["1.5", "2", "3", "Infinite"], c: 1, e: "Using the infinite sum formula S_∞ = a / (1 - r) with first term a = 1 and common ratio r = 1/2 gives: 1 / (1 - 1/2) = 2." },
            { id: "ns_m10", q: "The number of permutations of n different objects taken all at a time is:", a: ["n!", "(n-1)!", "n!/2", "n^n"], c: 0, e: "The total number of linear arrangements (permutations) of n distinct objects using all of them is given by ⁿP_n = n!." },
            { id: "ns_m11", q: "The slope of a line parallel to the x-axis is always:", a: ["1", "-1", "Undefined", "0"], c: 3, e: "A line parallel to the x-axis is completely horizontal, meaning its change in y (rise) is 0. Slope (m) = tan(0°) = 0." },
            { id: "ns_m12", q: "The derivative of cos(x) with respect to x is:", a: ["sin(x)", "-sin(x)", "sec²(x)", "-cos(x)"], c: 1, e: "By standard calculus differentiation rules, d/dx[cos(x)] = -sin(x)." },
            { id: "ns_m13", q: "The integral of 1/x with respect to x is:", a: ["ln|x| + c", "x + c", "-1/x² + c", "e^x + c"], c: 0, e: "Since the derivative of ln|x| is 1/x, the anti-derivative (integral) of 1/x dx is ln|x| + c." },
            { id: "ns_m14", q: "The distance of the point (3, 4) from the origin is:", a: ["5", "7", "25", "1"], c: 0, e: "Using the distance formula from origin (0,0): d = √(x² + y²) = √(3² + 4²) = √(9 + 16) = √25 = 5." },
            { id: "ns_m15", q: "If cos(x) = 0, then x is equal to:", a: ["0", "π", "π/2", "2π"], c: 2, e: "The cosine function evaluates to 0 at odd multiples of π/2. Among the options given, cos(π/2) = 0." },
            { id: "ns_m16", q: "The solution set of the equation x² + 1 = 0 in complex numbers is:", a: ["{1, -1}", "{i, -i}", "{0}", "Empty set"], c: 1, e: "Isolating the variable gives x² = -1. Taking the square root yields x = ±√(-1), which equals ±i. Thus, the set is {i, -i}." },
            { id: "ns_m17", q: "The arithmetic mean between a and b is given by:", a: ["√(ab)", "2ab/(a+b)", "(a+b)/2", "a-b"], c: 2, e: "The arithmetic mean (AM) represents the average value of two numbers, calculated using the standard expression (a + b) / 2." },
            { id: "ns_m18", q: "The geometric mean between 4 and 9 is:", a: ["6.5", "6", "13", "36"], c: 1, e: "The geometric mean (GM) of two positive numbers is calculated as GM = √(a · b). Here, √(4 · 9) = √36 = 6." },
            { id: "ns_m19", q: "The focus of the parabola y² = 4ax is located at:", a: ["(0, a)", "(a, 0)", "(-a, 0)", "(0, -a)"], c: 1, e: "For a standard right-ward opening parabola y² = 4ax with its vertex at the origin, the focus point is strictly along the x-axis at (a, 0)." },
            { id: "ns_m20", q: "The eccentricity of a circle is always:", a: ["1", "Greater than 1", "Less than 1", "0"], c: 3, e: "Eccentricity (e) measures structural deviation from a perfect circle. Because a circle has no deviation, its eccentricity value is 0." }
